body:
Whenever I use $fgets with a string input, I see the following error: 
 - $fgets's first argument must be a reg.

Sample code:

```
module testbench;
  integer fileIn;
  string msg;
  initial begin
    fileIn = $fopen("fileIn", "r");
    if (!fileIn) $error("BAD FILE");
    $fgets(msg, fileIn);
    $display("%s", msg);
    $fclose(fileIn);
  end
endmodule
```
Does Icarus support $fgets with string input? The code seems to work when using a different simulator on EDAPlayground.

Some more detail: This is running with Icarus v10.3 on Ubuntu 20.04.

